  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nIn the Lighthouse account manager currently the `validator-dir` flag needs to come _directly_ after the `validator` subcommand, which gives it quite poor UX and discoverability.\r\n\r\ni.e. you need to write\r\n\r\n```\r\nlighthouse account validator --validator-dir /path import --keystores /blah\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut can't write\r\n\r\n```\r\nlighthouse account validator import --validator-dir /path --keystores /blah\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse v3.3.0\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nI think there are options in `clap` (our CLI parser) to mark certain flags as global. I'm not sure if global is overkill though, I should hope it only applies from that subcommand _down_ and _not_ all the way up to the top-level `lighthouse` command.\r\n",
